# App restart workflow (ollama-dashboard)

When you change code that affects the running server, **restart the app yourself** — do not ask the user to restart it.

## Restart required

- Python under `app/` (routes, services, `__init__.py`, config)
- Jinja templates under `app/templates/`
- Environment or startup behavior (`wsgi.py`, `ollama_dashboard_cli.py`)

## Usually no restart (still tell user to hard-refresh)

- Static assets only (`app/static/css`, `app/static/js`, images) — Flask serves them on each request, but the browser may cache them.

## How to restart (Windows, this repo)

1. Stop any process on port 5000 if already running.
2. From repo root with venv active:
   - Release: `start.bat` (Waitress, production config)
   - Development: `start_dev.bat` (Flask debug reloader)
   - Or: `python ollama_dashboard_cli.py`
   - Automated restart (no pause): `restart_app.bat nopause` or set `OLLAMA_DASHBOARD_NO_PAUSE=1`
3. Run in background when continuing other work.
4. If restart fails with preflight/import errors, run `.venv\Scripts\pip install -r requirements.txt` then retry.

Default URL: http://127.0.0.1:5000

## After restart or static/CSS/JS changes

Tell the user to **refresh the web page** (hard refresh `Ctrl+F5` if CSS/JS looks stale) so visuals and client-side code update.
